longBusinessSummary: Stamford Land Corporation Ltd, an investment holding company, owns, operates, and manages hotels in Singapore, Australia, and the United Kingdom. It operates through five segments: Hotel Owning and Management, Property Development, Property Investment, Trading, and Others. The company owns and operates hotels and resorts under the Sir Stamford at Circular Quay, Stamford Plaza Sydney Airport, Stamford Plaza Melbourne, Stamford Grand Adelaide, Stamford Plaza Adelaide, and Stamford Plaza Brisbane names. It also invests in, develops, constructs, rents, manages, and trades in real estate properties. In addition, the company provides interior decoration, trustee, travel agency, and management services. Further, it invests in securities; and provides treasury functions. The company was formerly known as Hai Sun Hup Group Ltd. Stamford Land Corporation Ltd was founded in 1935 and is based in Singapore.
